A simple tool to chunk up a file into multiple parts.

Usage: chunker [options] target_file

Specific options:
    -v, --verbose                    Run verbosely
    -c, --chunk-size=SIZE            Size of chunks to create. Default: 800 MB
    -o, --overlap-size=SIZE          Overlap size for each chunk. Default 0 MB
    -b, --begin-offset=OFFSET        Begin chunking the file after the specified OFFSET MBytes
    -e, --end-offset=OFFSET          End chunking the file at OFFSET MBytes from the end of the file
    -d, --destination=DIR            Directory to store the chunked files into

Common options:
    -h, --help                       Show this message
        --version                    Show version
